bcl:definition.bcl:text:
    electric motor means a machine which converts electrical power into
rotational mechanical power and includes any such machine that is incorporated into any
other product;

    enclosed motor means an electric motor constructed in such a manner
as to prevent the free exchange of air between the inside and outside of the case, but
the case is not sufficiently enclosed to be termed airtight;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
that is enclosed in a case that will withstand the explosion of any flammable
              gas or material that may enter the case, without being damaged and without
              transmitting an explosion to the outside;

bcl:definition.bcl:text:
    IP code means an alpha numeric sequence indicating the degree of
protection offered by a motor's enclosure to foreign object insertion and water ingress,
as defined by MG1-5.2;

    open motor means an electric motor with ventilating openings that
permit passage of external cooling air over and around the windings of the
motor;

bcl:subparagraph.bcl:text:
meets the standard operating characteristics requirements, as set out in
                  subsection (2), and standard mechanical construction requirements, as
                described in subsection (3);

